md:note.div:
Digtsamling af den osmaniske kvindelige poet Moralīzade Hamit Leyla Hanīm (d. 1847) kendt som Leyla Hanim. Digtsamlingen, Divan, var trykt i Bulaq (Kairo) 1844.
I en note på side 15 noterer trykkeren, at han for første gang har anvendt en helt ny tryktype af Ta'liq skriften, og at han synes at teksten derfor har fået et meget smukt udtryk.
OS-237

Leyla Moralīzade Hamit (d. 1847), known as Layla Hanīm was a Turkish poetess and wrote her poems in Ottoman Turkish. The poetry collection, Divan, was printed in Bulaq (Cairo) in 1844 with a set of types in Ta'liq script. The printer has added an endnote on p. 15 commenting on the beauty of the text and informing that the set of types was new and used here the very first time.
